26/05/2011
ANKARA, Turkey -- Police say at least seven people were injured by an explosion in Istanbul on Thursday (May 26th). It happened at a bus stop near a shopping mall in the Etiler district during the busy morning commute. Police say a midsize bomb was attached to a bike. Witnesses say the explosion unleashed a plume of yellow smoke. No group has claimed responsibility yet. (Anadolu news agency, CNN Turk, World Bulletin - 26/05/11)
